      "notes": "Dacian/Thracian substrate: pre-Roman Balkan IE languages. Possibly explains central vowels /ə, ɨ/, postposed article, and ~100 Romanian-Albanian shared words of unknown origin (e.g. copil, moș, viezure). Exact Dacian phonology unrecoverable."
    }
